narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a good class, I got a lot out of it. Be prepared to give your fellow students feedback.
You have to take it, so take it! It's a nice thing to have every week to keep your head in the game for you senior project.

Senior Art majors work on independent projects throughout the semester. Each student presents to the group twice during weekly crits, once at the beginning of their project and once around the mid-point. At the end of the semester, the work goes up in the senior thesis show in Green Gallery. I would highly recommend the course. I grew a lot from the experience. Each student has an advisor to guide you through the process, but its up to you to on top of your work. Don't procrastinate!
